tial of his art than any of his colleagues." This profound contemplation of his art is superbly captured in the pieces from all periods of Hitchcock’s career gathered in this volume, which reveal fascinating details about how he envisioned and attempted to create a "pure cinema" that was entertaining, commercially successful, and artistically ambitious and innovative in an environment that did not always support this lofty goal.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aMotion picture industry. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / General.2bisacsh  a20th century film history.  aalfred hitchcock.  aart of cinema.  aart.  aartists.  acareer.  acinema.  acollection of interviews.  adial m for murder.  adirectors.  aearly fiction.  aenglish film director.  aenglish producer.  afilm industry.  afilm.  afilmmakers.  afilmmaking techniques.  afilmmaking.  ahistory of cinema.  ahitchcockian.  ainfluential directors.  ainnovative.  ainsightful.  amaster of suspense.  amovies.  anorth by northwest.  aoriginality.  apsycho.  apure cinema.  arear window.  astrangers on a train.  avertigo.1 aBurford, Roger, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDavidson, Bill, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGottlieb, Sidney, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLeider, R. Allen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMacklin, Anthony, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTwiggar, Beth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete Package 2014-2015z97831106211120 cprintz978052027958240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052096039840uhttps: